<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOODBYS TO THE SHOE, FOND AND OTHERWISE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
If I still had all the money I've lost wagering on favorites ridden by Bill 
Shoemaker plus the cash he's beaten me out of atop longshots, I could retire, 
too. 
</P>
<P>
Now that the Shoe is calling it a career, do you think he would consider 
spending his retirement standing out in my front yard in his jockey silks? I 
think he owes me that much. 
</P>
<P>
CHARLES M. ROSE, Temple City 
</P>
</TEXT>
