<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE RELATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding Michael Wilmington's Jan. 12 review of "Internal Affairs": 
</P>
<P>
I wonder if a more sensitive reviewer or a more aware (daring?) movie maker 
would have questioned the screenwriter's gratuitous use of a "lesbian partner" 
as a police officer. 
</P>
<P>
I can almost picture the studio conferences over this issue: 
</P>
<P>
"Let's have a woman partner -- that's 'in.' " 
</P>
<P>
"OK, but we can't have another love interest subplot -- let's make her a 
lesbian, that's sexually safe and 'in'!" 
</P>
<P>
And did even one rational voice suggest that maybe a good-looking heterosexual 
man and an attractive heterosexual woman can work together, professionally and 
respectfully , without "doing it"? Oh, no, that's dull city, eh, guys? 
</P>
<P>
PHYLLIS MAGILL LEVY, Mission Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
