<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
ALASKA; 
</P>
<P>
JURY SELECTED FOR EXXON VALDEZ CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A jury of seven women and five men was selected in the trial of Joseph 
Hazelwood, who was the skipper aboard the Exxon Valdez when it hit a reef and 
caused the nation's worst oil spill. 
</P>
<P>
Lawyers settled on the panel of 12 by midday, but questioning continued to seat 
three alternates in the case. The jury was to be officially impaneled Monday 
and opening statements will follow. Prosecution and defense lawyers quizzed 52 
prospective jurors before settling on the 12 citizens who will spend the next 
several weeks hearing testimony and considering evidence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
