beliefs -- and, therefore, the right to refuse as leaders, those who do not 
share their beliefs. This fundamental right to choice of leader is what both 
Protestantism and democracy are all about. So-called "liberalism," it would 
seem, can also attempt dictatorship. 
</P>
<P>
N.E. DE LARA 
