<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: PARK CHANGES TO BE DISCUSSED AT MEETINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Santa Monica Mountains Conservancy has announced a series of public 
meetings to discuss additions and improvements to parks and trails in the Rim 
of the Valley Corridor. 
</P>
<P>
The Mountains Conservancy is a state agency that acquires parkland in the Santa 
Monica Mountains and other hills and mountains that ring the San Fernando and 
Crescenta valleys. 
</P>
<P>
Citizens are invited to the public meetings to recommend additions to the 
network of trails and parks being established in the Santa Monica, Verdugo and 
Santa Susana mountains and the Simi Hills. 
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, the meeting for the Thousand Oaks-Simi Valley-Moorpark area will be 
held at 7 p.m. at the East Valley sheriff's station community room, 2101 East 
Olsen Road, Thousand Oaks. 
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, the Granada Hills-Mission Hills-Northridge-Chatsworth-Sylmar area 
meeting will be at 3 p.m. at the Granada Hills branch library, Chatsworth 
Street and Petit Avenue, Granada Hills. 
</P>
<P>
On Monday, Feb. 26, the Santa Clarita-Granada Hills area meeting will be held 
at the Towsley Canyon Park Visitor Center, 24255 The Old Road, near the 
Calgrove exit of Interstate 5 in the Santa Clarita Valley. 
</P>
</TEXT>
