<HEADLINE>
<P>
$200,000 FIRE BLAMED ON ELECTRICAL SHORT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An electrical short started a fire that caused $200,000 damage at a Glendale 
business, fire officials said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
About 100 firefighters from Glendale, Burbank and Los Angeles fought the fire 
at Cal Best Ceiling, in the 1900 block of Gardena Avenue, which was reported at 
11:37 p.m. Thursday, said Mike Hand of the Verdugo dispatch center. 
</P>
<P>
Flames burned through the roof before they were extinguished early Friday, Hand 
said. The blaze caused $100,000 damage to the building and $100,000 to its 
contents, Hand said. 
</P>
<P>
No injuries were reported. Hand said investigators determined the cause was an 
electrical malfunction. 
