<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BASKETBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In other boys' games: 
</P>
<P>
Royal 78, Channel Islands 74 -- Russell Myers scored 27 points to lead Royal 
(19-5, 8-2) to a Marmonte League victory at home. 
</P>
<P>
Royal took a 54-38 lead with 3 minutes 30 seconds left in the third quarter, 
but Channel Islands (7-15,1-10) came back, tying the score, 63-63, with 5:14 
remaining. 
</P>
<P>
Royal pulled away again with an 8-0 run at the five-minute mark in the fourth 
quarter with three quick baskets by Myers. 
</P>
<P>
Marlow Durmiendo scored 32 points to lead Channel Islands. 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks 62, Westlake 61 -- Chris Loll made a 13-foot jump shot with 13 
seconds left to give Thousand Oaks (11-10, 6-4) an upset victory at home. 
</P>
<P>
Westlake's chances ended when Matt Heckmann (12 points) missed a 17-foot jump 
shot with four seconds left. Westlake fell to 13-8 and 7-3, a game behind 
first-place Royal (8-2) in league play. 
</P>
<P>
Loll finished with a game-high 20 points and 12 rebounds. Sophomore Shane 
Graham had 13 points for Thousand Oaks. 
</P>
<P>
Canyon 67, Ridgecrest Burroughs 41 -- Tom Boobar's 17 points led four Cowboys 
in double figures in a Golden League game at Canyon. Mike Dobes had 12 points, 
Jermaine Nixon 10 and Reggie Haggans 15 off the bench for Canyon (16-6, 5-3). 
</P>
<P>
Ridgecrest Burroughs guard Matt Duncan topped all scorers with 20 as the Burros 
fell to 2-16, 1-7. 
</P>
<P>
St. Francis 59, Alemany 58 -- Rich Dice scored 17 points for Alemany (7-15, 
1-6), but missed the front end of a one-and-one situation with six seconds 
left. William Burr and Ray Awad had 14 and 13 points for Alemany. 
</P>
<P>
Harvard 76, Chaminade 64 -- Rick Osterloh had only four baskets, but he hit 16 
of 18 free throws, including 10 of 11 in the fourth period, as Harvard (19-2, 
8-0) pulled away in the San Fernando Valley League game at Chaminade. Osterloh 
finished with 24 points, and Matt Clark and Mike Wolf added 17 and 14 points. 
</P>
<P>
Chaminade (10-10, 4-4), which pulled to within 62-56 in the fourth period, 
received 18 points from Charlie Fei and 16 from Mark Mirkovich. 
</P>
<P>
Bell-Jeff 56, St. Genevieve 36 -- Bryan Camacho and Brian Lee scored 13 and 12 
points to lead Bell-Jeff (9-11, 5-3) to the San Fernando Valley League win. 
</P>
<P>
Notre Dame 73, La Salle 47 -- Paul Hewitt scored 22 points to lead the Knights 
(10-8, 4-2) to the San Fernando Valley League win at home. 
</P>
<P>
Agoura 47, Calabasas 37 -- Sean Martin scored 16 points to lead Agoura in a 
Frontier League game at Calabasas. 
</P>
<P>
L.A. Baptist 50, Maranatha 44 -- Alex Pistone scored 16 points to lead L.A. 
Baptist to an Alpha League victory over host Maranatha. After leading, 11-8, in 
the first quarter, L.A. Baptist rebounded, building an 18-point lead in the 
fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Anthony Fisher and Matt Lindbolm each had 14 points for Maranatha. 
</P>
<P>
Faith Baptist 71, Buckley 59 -- Sophomore center Peter Rasmussen scored 26 
points and had 21 rebounds to lead Faith Baptist (13-9, 6-2) in the Delphic 
League game. Rasmussen was eight of 12 from the field and 10 of 11 from the 
line. 
</P>
<P>
Bishop 74, Paraclete 63 -- Junior center Shawn Preasmyer scored 14 points, 
grabbed 15 rebounds and had six blocks, but host Paraclete (8-12, 1-7) fell in 
a Desert-Inyo League game at Antelope Valley College. 
</P>
<P>
Highland Hall 70, South Bay Lutheran 66 (OT) -- Senior guard Bob Ramirez scored 
26 points, including five of the Hawks' 10 points in overtime, to help Highland 
Hall (18-2, 12-0) clinch the Westside League title at Stonehurst Park. Craig 
Ernst (21 points and 14 rebounds) sank a free throw with eight seconds left in 
regulation to force overtime. 
</P>
<P>
Greg Anastas had 11 points and 11 rebounds and John Klejnot had 12 rebounds for 
the Hawks. 
</P>
<P>
Brentwood 71, Campbell Hall 64 -- Chris Scott scored 12 of his 19 points in the 
first half as the Eagles raced to a 37-16 lead at intermission in a Delphic 
League game at Campbell Hall as the Vikings remained winless in league play. 
</P>
<P>
Grant 75, Poly 54 -- Grant, which shot 57% from the field, jumped to a 16-5 
lead after one period and led 37-17 at halftime in rolling to its eighth East 
Valley League win without a loss. Keith Weinstein led Grant (18-3) with 24 
points and Setro Terzian added 17. 
</P>
<P>
Monroe 85, Van Nuys 52 -- Kenyon Wright (22 points) and Maurice McIntosh (18) 
combined for 40 points to lead Monroe to a Mid-Valley League win. Elmer Singh 
added 12 points for Monroe (4-13, 3-5). James Hooks had 11 points off the bench 
for Van Nuys (2-17, 1-7), and Michael Crawford added 10. 
</P>
<P>
GIRLS 
</P>
<P>
Grant 53, Poly 23 -- Junior center Shenia Smith scored a game-high 23 points to 
lead Grant (8-4, 4-0) to an East Valley League win at home. Monique Young added 
eight points and 10 steals for Grant. 
</P>
<P>
Van Nuys 71, Monroe 22 -- Leading 33-9 at the half, Van Nuys (17-3, 8-0) routed 
Monroe (1-7) in a Mid-Valley League game at home. Senior center Stacie Toon had 
19 points and 14 rebounds to lead Van Nuys. 
</P>
<P>
Highland Hall 38, South Bay Lutheran 31 (OT) -- Behind 17 points from Kristen 
Johansen, Highland Hall clinched at least a share of its first league title 
with a Westside League victory. 
</P>
<P>
Laura Kenney scored four of her eight points in overtime for Highland Hall 
(12-5, 3-0). 
</P>
</TEXT>
