<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND CHECKLIST FOR DIGGERS AND PLANTERS: GARDENING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen: 
</P>
<P>
* If your houseplants are dropping leaves, overwatering could be the cause. 
</P>
<P>
During the winter, they need less water because there are fewer hours of 
daylight. 
</P>
<P>
* It's not too late to add more color to the winter garden. Check to see which 
plants are in bloom at the nursery. 
</P>
<P>
* While pruning roses, be sure to discard the old leaves and branches so they 
won't become a home for insects and diseases. 
</P>
<P>
* If you have a cool-season lawn (rye, blue, fine or tall fescue) and live in 
one of the warmer local climate zones, you'll probably need to mow it once or 
twice a week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
