<HEADLINE>
<P>
GRAF BREEZES TO 50TH CONSECUTIVE WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TOKYO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Steffi Graf extended her singles winning streak to 50 matches today by breezing 
past Soviet Larisa Savchenko, 6-0, 6-3, in the quarterfinals of the Pan Pacific 
tennis tournament. 
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old West German, the world's top-ranked women's player, needed only 
51 minutes to beat Savchenko, ranked 23rd. 
</P>
<P>
"I had expected a much harder match because she is really a tough player," Graf 
said. "On this surface it could have been a much closer match because she 
usually has a big serve. But she made simple mistakes." 
</P>
<P>
Graf meets Manuela Maleeva of Switzerland in the semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
Maleeva, ranked eighth in the world, beat big-serving Brenda Schultz of The 
Netherlands, 6-2, 6-0. In another quarterfinal match, second-seeded Arantxa 
Sanchez of Spain downed American Gigi Fernandez, 1-6, 6-1, 6-2. 
</P>
</TEXT>
