<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: COLEMAN SUES HIS MOTHER FOR MALICIOUS 
PROSECUTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Actor Gary Coleman filed a malicious prosecution lawsuit Friday in Los Angeles 
against his mother, two days after a judge turned down her attempt to have a 
conservator appointed to take control of his affairs. 
</P>
<P>
Coleman, former star of the television sitcom "Diff'rent Strokes," claims 
Edmonia Sue Coleman knew the claims she made in the conservatorship petition -- 
that her son's nearly $7-million estate was being mismanaged and the actor's 
kidney condition was not being properly treated -- were false when the court 
papers were filed in December, 1989. 
</P>
<P>
Gary Coleman's suit claims his mother sought a trustee for him in retaliation 
for a separate lawsuit he filed last June against her and others, accusing them 
of misappropriating $1 million from his estate from 1985 to 1988. Gary 
Coleman's new suit asks for $25,000 in damages. 
</P>
</TEXT>
