<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST : SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 32-year-old man died in a house fire early Friday while sleeping in a small, 
detached bedroom, the San Diego Fire Department reported. 
</P>
<P>
Firefighters found Kim May, 32, dead in a corner of the bedroom, which had once 
been a detached single-car garage. A bed, a laundry hamper and a space heater 
were in room at 2827 Lincoln Ave. 
</P>
<P>
At 2:49 a.m., Jerry May, the victim's brother, discovered the fire when he 
heard screams for help, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The fire was caused by the space heater, authorities said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
