<HEADLINE>
<P>
OLYMPIC LEAGUE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
ORANGE LUTHERAN SPARED BY MISSED THREE-POINTER, 72-69 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB BORSUM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ORANGE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ruben Oronoz hit three three-point baskets for Whittier Christian, but the one 
he missed in the final 10 seconds helped decide Friday's game with Orange 
Lutheran. 
</P>
<P>
Orange Lutheran defeated Whittier Christian, 72-69, at Orange Lutheran High. 
Matt Bode's two free throws in the final seven seconds and Daryl Cole's steal 
at the buzzer ensured the Lancers' victory. 
</P>
<P>
The schools are tied for second place in the Olympic League with 7-4 records. 
Orange Lutheran (13-9 overall) hosts first-place Valley Christian at 7:30 
tonight. 
</P>
<P>
"This was a tight game and the team that made the fewest mistakes won it," 
Whittier Christian Coach Bob Brown said. 
</P>
<P>
Whittier Christian's Kevin Wilch attempted to tie the game with a three-pointer 
in the final seconds but he lost the ball to Cole. 
</P>
<P>
"The ball just slipped out of his hands and went into my hands," said Cole. 
Cole, who had 29 points, hit five three-point baskets in the first half and had 
four rebounds for the game. 
</P>
<P>
"Daryl just seems to do what needs to be done at the right time," Orange 
Lutheran Coach Jerry Simmons said. "It's nice to have a shooter who can do so 
many things." 
</P>
<P>
For Orange Lutheran, Brian Bedord had 12 points and 10 rebounds, Bode had seven 
points and six assists, and Luke Aucoin had seven assists. 
</P>
<P>
Dan Long scored 20 points, Oronoz had 17 and Joe Kostantarakis 16 for Whittier 
Christian (11-10). 
</P>
<P>
Santa Margarita 70, Ontario Christian 65 -- Santa Margarita made 13 of 15 free 
throws in the final quarter and shot 51% from the field to remain tied for 
third place in the eight-team league. Dan Bathey scored 22 points and teammate 
Mike Carpenter added 15 points and six steals for Santa Margarita (9-11, 6-5). 
</P>
<P>
Brethren 74, Capistrano Valley Christian 59 -- Forward Chiron Hart scored 15 
points for visiting Brethren (14-6, 7-4). Nathan Owens and Chris Elliott each 
scored 16 points for Capistrano Valley Christian (8-12, 2-9). 
</P>
</TEXT>
