<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE LEAGUE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
RANCHO ALAMITOS PRESSES THE ISSUE AGAINST GARDEN GROVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rancho Alamitos High School applied its full-court press to perfection Friday 
night, reeling off 29 consecutive points in the second quarter, and went on to 
a 101-73 victory over visiting Garden Grove. 
</P>
<P>
"That's the way we practice it," Rancho Alamitos Coach Eric Hamamoto said of 
the scoring streak, "but you never expect the press to create that kind of 
run." 
</P>
<P>
Although he didn't score a point, Oscar Ramirez, a 5-foot-6 guard, keyed the 
scoring run with five steals. 
</P>
<P>
"Defense is what I do best," Ramirez said. "Lately, I've been sitting out a 
lot, but getting back in there tonight and helping the team felt good." 
</P>
<P>
Garden Grove kept the score close early, closing to 22-21 on Bob Ioja's layup 
moments into the second quarter. Ioja finished with 24 points. 
</P>
<P>
But the Vaqueros responded with their spree to take a 51-21 lead with 3:15 left 
in the half. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Alamitos (16-4 overall, 10-1 in league play) remained tied for first 
place in the Garden Grove League with Kennedy. 
</P>
<P>
Garden Grove (9-11, 7-4) scored just seven points in the second quarter, making 
three of 18 shots from the field. Rancho Alamitos also forced 11 turnovers in 
the quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Paul Pruess sank four of eight three-point shots and finished with 26 points 
for the Vaqueros. David Green added 21 points for Rancho Alamitos, and Mark 
Perry had 18 points for Garden Grove. 
</P>
<P>
In other league games: 
</P>
<P>
Santiago 59, La Quinta 56 (OT) -- Van Trung banked in a 40-foot shot at the 
buzzer to give Santiago (7-12, 3-8) the victory at La Quinta. Paul Hastings hit 
a turnaround jump shot from five feet with 18 seconds left in regulation to 
send the game into overtime for La Quinta (0-19, 0-11). 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy 72, Los Amigos 43 -- Jim Barker had 27 points and nine rebounds and 
Jermaine Galloway had 12 points and nine rebounds to lead host Kennedy (13-6, 
10-1). 
</P>
<P>
Bolsa Grande 60, Pacifica 54 -- Hinh Bui scored 21 points to lead visiting 
Bolsa Grande (7-11, 5-6). 
</P>
</TEXT>
