<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
KENNEDY LOSES BIG LEAD BUT WINS ANYWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kennedy High School lost an 18-point lead after three quarters but managed to 
defeat Los Amigos, 57-55, in a Garden Grove League girls' basketball game 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy put reserve players into the game and stopped using a full-court press 
and Los Amigos outscored Kennedy, 22-6, in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Guards Michelle Harris and Valerie Ruiz each had 19 points and combined to make 
12 steals for host Kennedy (11-10, 7-4). 
</P>
<P>
May Ly had nine of her 21 points in the fourth quarter for Los Amigos, which 
dropped to 5-6 in league. 
</P>
<P>
In other Garden Grove League games: 
</P>
<P>
La Quinta 73, Santiago 17 -- Amy Jalewalia had 31 points, 13 rebounds and six 
steals, and Heather Brannan had 27 points, nine rebounds and four steals to 
lead La Quinta (20-2, 11-0), which won its 51st consecutive league game. Jodi 
Cole had no points but had seven rebounds and seven assists for La Quinta. 
Becky Elcock had 11 of Santiago's 17 points. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Alamitos 62, Garden Grove 42 -- Jenny Newsome had 24 points for Rancho 
Alamitos (15-3, 9-2) at home. Shellie Tsuji added 12 and Melinda Lira had 11 
for Rancho Alamitos. Melanie Dear scored 12 for Garden Grove (6-5 in league). 
Garden Grove led, 13-3, after the first quarter and 22-19 at the half. But 
Rancho Alamitos outscored Garden Grove, 23-8, in the third quarter. 
</P>
